The paper deals with visual saliency prediction, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed model uses conditional generative adversarial networks (GANs), which are a popular tool in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The model also incorporates memory architectures, which are a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of contextual semantics and relationships, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL).
